class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525684\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2525684\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ahd1665702917174.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ahd1665702917174.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ahd1665702917174.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ahd1665702917174\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Update an existing record.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__section_n1y_zlr_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d515208e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130688e1_d130689e1_d130690e1\">All fields in the record must be updated. There is no\n        information available about which fields have been modified.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130691e1_d130692e1_d130693e1\">For SQL-like DBMSs, the connector must use the ‘if’\n        list. This identifies exactly one record by either the primary key or the PRA, and\n        optionally a U_VERSION field.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130694e1_d130695e1_d130696e1\">For ISAM-like or record-level DBMSs, a Fetch mode 2\n        has prepared locking and positioning. The positioned record is the record to be updated.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130697e1_d130698e1_d130699e1\">Build the concatenated primary key, if required.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__section_h4l_ncy_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d515208e68\">From Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Preconditions realized by Uniface—the table that the Update is requested for is open.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Available from Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;TMEnabled</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Indicates whether the connector is\n                TM-controlled.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrv</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Points to the connector workspace if a workspace was\n                requested in the Info request.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrvini</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Unique identification of the current logon\n                path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;iobuf</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Points to the new data for the record.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udatlen</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Length of the data pointed to by\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;iobuf</code>.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;ufldlst</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Field list that describes all the fields in the\n                table.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;uiflst</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Identifies the record to be updated.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;uilist</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">Points to the index list.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;vsfnr</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15638e1_d15639e1_d15640e1__entry__2\">If <code class=\"ph codeph\">vsfnr</code> equals 0, segmented fields\n                do not have to be updated, otherwise they do have to be updated.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__section_zky_ncy_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d515208e207\">To Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The concatenated primary key must be added to the hitlist by means of the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">uaddhit</code> service function.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130712e1_d130713e1_d130714e1\">If the DBMS supports PRAs and the PRA of the record\n        changed as a result of the Update, the new PRA must be added to the hitlist by means of the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">uaddhit</code> service function.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Request Return Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__2\">Exactly one record was updated successfully.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__1\">-2</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__2\">Specified record does not exist.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__1\">-6</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__2\">Exceptional error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__1\">-9</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__2\">I/O server logon error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__1\">-16</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ahd1665702917174__table_d15641e1_d15642e1_d15643e1__entry__2\">DBMS reported network error.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130715e1_d130716e1_d130717e1\">When the connector request return value is less than\n        0, an error code must be supplied in <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code>. When more than one\n        record or zero records have been updated, the connector must return an error.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__section_x51_2mr_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d515208e304\">Service functions</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__ul_wtc_fmr_gwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__li_d46883e1_d46884e1_d46885e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"phf1665702917888.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/phf1665702917888.html\" title=\"ubldprim builds the concatenated primary key for a record.\">ubldprim</a>\n</code>—build the primary key in user-supplied buffer. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__li_d46886e1_d46887e1_d46888e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wcr1665702917956.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wcr1665702917956.html\" title=\"ubldprm builds the concatenated primary key for a record.\">ubldprm</a>\n</code>—build the primary key in the SQL buffer. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__section_olc_dmr_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d515208e343\">Extra information</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130724e1_d130725e1_d130726e1\">Uniface assumes that the DBMS checks the uniqueness of\n        keys in unique indexes (Uniface primary key and candidate keys).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130727e1_d130728e1_d130729e1\">When the connector has to update segmented fields\n          (<code class=\"ph codeph\">vsfnr</code> is not equal to 0) the segments of the segmented field have to be\n        obtained directly from the Uniface kernel using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ugetblob</code> service\n        function.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__section_mtv_fmr_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d515208e362\">TM-Controlled Connectors</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ahd1665702917174__p_d130733e1_d130734e1_d130735e1\">TM-controlled connectors are not allowed to begin,\n        commit, or rollback transactions.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azl1665702915888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uctrl</a><p>Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/afo1665702918517.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ugetblob</a><p>Get segmented data from the Uniface kernel.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrb1665702976299.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors</a><p>A database connector can be controlled by a transaction manager only if it is TM-capable. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. However, you can use the APIs provided by the Database Connector Interface to build a custom database connector that does.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525684\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525684\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Update (U) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Update an existing record. Description All fields in the record must be updated. There is no information available about which fields have been modified. For SQL-like DBMSs, the connector must use the ‘if’ list. This identifies exactly one record by either the primary key or the PRA, and optionally a U_VERSION field. For ISAM-like or record-level DBMSs, a Fetch mode 2 has prepared locking and positioning. The positioned record is the record to be updated. Build the concatenated primary key, if required. From Uniface Preconditions realized by Uniface—the table that the Update is requested for is open. Table 1. Information Available from Uniface Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->TMEnabled Indicates whether the connector is TM-controlled. uctrl->udrv Points to the connector workspace if a workspace was requested in the Info request. uctrl->udrvini Unique identification of the current logon path. uctrl->iobuf Points to the new data for the record. uctrl->udatlen Length of the data pointed to by uctrl->iobuf . uctrl->ufldlst Field list that describes all the fields in the table. uctrl->uiflst Identifies the record to be updated. uctrl->uilist Points to the index list. uctrl->vsfnr If vsfnr equals 0, segmented fields do not have to be updated, otherwise they do have to be updated. To Uniface The concatenated primary key must be added to the hitlist by means of the uaddhit service function. If the DBMS supports PRAs and the PRA of the record changed as a result of the Update, the new PRA must be added to the hitlist by means of the uaddhit service function. Table 2. Connector Request Return Values Value Description 0 Exactly one record was updated successfully. -2 Specified record does not exist. -6 Exceptional error. -9 I/O server logon error. -16 DBMS reported network error. When the connector request return value is less than 0, an error code must be supplied in uctrl->udrverr . When more than one record or zero records have been updated, the connector must return an error. Service functions ubldprim —build the primary key in user-supplied buffer. ubldprm —build the primary key in the SQL buffer. Extra information Uniface assumes that the DBMS checks the uniqueness of keys in unique indexes (Uniface primary key and candidate keys). When the connector has to update segmented fields ( vsfnr is not equal to 0) the segments of the segmented field have to be obtained directly from the Uniface kernel using the ugetblob service function. TM-Controlled Connectors TM-controlled connectors are not allowed to begin, commit, or rollback transactions. Related Links uctrl Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table. ugetblob Get segmented data from the Uniface kernel. TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors A database connector can be controlled by a transaction manager only if it is TM-capable. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. However, you can use the APIs provided by the Database Connector Interface to build a custom database connector that does. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}